C
r(t)=30\sqrt{\cos(2t)}
{\rm d}s
s'(t)=\sqrt{r^2(t)+r'^2(t)}={30\over\sqrt{\cos(2t)}}={30^2\over r(t)}\ ,
|y| ds=r(t)\ |\sin t|\ {30^2\over r(t)}=30^2|\sin t|\ dt\ ,
\int_C|y|\ {\rm d}s=2\cdot30^2\cdot\int_{-\pi/4}^{\pi/4}|\sin t|\ dt=1800\bigl(2-\sqrt{2}\bigr)\ .
